		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>
				<strong>Do I need to talk to my bank before moving?</strong>
				<br>
				Yes, it would be advisable to check with your bank what your daily/weekly and monthly withdrawal limits are when you are abroad.
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>Do I need to provide any paperwork before moving?</strong>
				<br>
				Yes, we need a copy of your passport to prepare the paperwork for your residencia in Spain. Without the residencia you cannot work in Spain, you will also not be able to get internet and a mobile on contract.
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>What do I do to get health coverage in Spain?</strong>
				<br>
				If you are employed by a Danish company, you need to apply for the A1/E101 document with Udbetaling Danmark. You need to bring that document AND your European Health Card.
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>Do we need to facilitate any other information?</strong>
				<br>
				Yes, we need the first name of your mother and father, again for the NIE/Residencia application. We would also need your telephone number.
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>I have children who are moving with me, what documentation do I need to bring?</strong>
				<br>
				You need to bring, birth certificate plus a certified spanish translation and their passports
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>Where can I have the translations best done?</strong>
				<br>
				It's probably cheaper to have the translations done in Spain, and you'll have it back normally within 48 hours.
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>How do I go about getting an NIE/Residencia?</strong>
				<br>
				We can recommend you to someone we are working with at the moment who will guide you effortless throught the entire process of getting your NIE/Residencia, setting up bank account and ordering your internet at home and/or mobile contract.
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>How much would that cost?</strong>
				<br>
				For 80€ all this can be done plus the 10,50 € for the taxes to get the NIE/Residencia
			</li>
			<br>
			<li>
				<strong>How much cost internet at home plus a mobile contract?</strong>
				<br>
				Costs vary depending on your needs, however we find that most people who want internet at home plus a mobile can get a a deal between 30€ - 50€. To get internet at home, you need to install a landline (in most cases), internet is unlimited. If you make international calls, the bill will go up, but there are a lot of other ways to call back home without increasing your phone bill.
			</li>
			<br>
		</ol>
